Contrary to its name, Iceland is not a winter wasteland. It is however, an expanse of unblemished beauty marooned between the Atlantic and the Arctic. Unlike its European counterparts, Iceland has remained immune from the chaos surrounding global politics. The Nordic island, streamlined with active volcanoes and hot springs is a hotspot for exploration junkies. The people compliment the alluring nature of the country with their resourcefulness and cultural awareness. Tracts of beauty in the very next corner you turn, Iceland is not just a country stuck in an ocean, it is an experience one should not mull over. 